.TH NHOPKG 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg \- universal binary and source package manager for GNU/Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhopkg
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIPACKAGE...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhopkg\fR is a universal package manager that works on any GNU/Linux
distribution. It supports binary packages (\fI.nho\fR) and source packages
(\fI.srcnho\fR). Packages can be installed locally or fetched from remote
repositories.
.P
Administrative tasks (repository management, source package creation, user
management) are handled by companion tools: \fBnhopkg-src\fR, \fBnhopkg-repos\fR,
\fBnhouser\fR, and \fBnhopkg-overlay\fR.
.SH COMMANDS
Exactly one command may be specified per invocation.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-install \fI<file.nho>\fR
Install a local \fI.nho\fR binary package.
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-super-install, \-d, \-\-dios \fI<package>\fR
Install a package from a remote repository with automatic dependency resolution.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-build \fI<file.srcnho>\fR
Build and install a source \fI.srcnho\fR package. Downloads sources, applies
patches, runs nbuild(), ninstall(), and creates/installs the binary \fI.nho\fR.
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-super-build \fI<name>\fR
Clone a remote Git repository and build/install from its \fInhoid\fR recipe.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-remove \fI<package>\fR
Remove an installed package.
.TP
.B \-\-purge \fI<package>\fR
Remove a package plus all packages that depend on it.
.TP
.B \-B, \-\-backup \fI<package>\fR
Recreate a \fI.nho\fR binary package from an already-installed package.
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List all packages installed by nhopkg.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-info \fI<package>\fR
Show detailed information about a package (searches installed, repository,
and local \fI.nho\fR files).
.TP
.B \-w, \-\-show \fI<package>\fR
List every file owned by an installed package.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-search \fI<pattern>\fR
Search for packages in local repository metadata.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-list-repo [\fI<repo>\fR]
List all packages available in configured repositories. Optionally filter by
repository name.
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-check \fI<package>\fR
Verify the integrity of an installed package (checks every listed file exists).
.TP
.B \-y, \-\-upgrade
Upgrade all installed packages to the latest version available in repositories.
.TP
.B \-U, \-\-update
Synchronise all configured repository databases.
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-update-db
Rebuild the local file-location database via updatedb/plocate.
.TP
.B \-x, \-\-update-shooters
Refresh system caches: GLib schemas, icon cache, desktop database, MIME
database, man pages, font cache, shared library cache, GDK pixbuf loaders.
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-clean
Remove cached \fI.nho\fR packages from the download cache. With \fB\-R\fR also
cleans the build directory.
.TP
.B \-G, \-\-install-group \fI<group>\fR
Install every package belonging to a named group (e.g. base, libs, xorg)
across all active repositories.
.TP
.B \-X, \-\-strip-binaries
Strip debug symbols from ELF binaries during \fB\-\-build\fR (experimental).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B \-R, \-\-recursive
Answer "yes" to all prompts (non-interactive mode). With \fB\-e\fR also cleans
the build directory.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIDIR\fR
Write command output (list, info, show) to a log file in \fIDIR\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-root \fIDIR\fR
Operate on an alternate root directory (for bootstrap, chroot, or containers).
Post-install hooks are written to a generated script rather than executed.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-deps
Skip dependency resolution.
.TP
.B \-\-force-check-deps
Force dependency resolution even if disabled in configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-arch
Skip architecture validation.
.TP
.B \-\-force-check-arch
Force architecture validation even if disabled in configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-sha256, \-\-no-check-sums
Skip SHA-256 checksum verification.
.TP
.B \-\-force-check-sha256, \-\-force-check-sums
Force checksum verification even if disabled in configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-sign-package
Sign the binary package with GPG during \fB\-\-build\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-no-sign-package
Skip GPG signing during \fB\-\-build\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-verify-package-signature
Verify the GPG signature of a package before installing it.
.TP
.B \-\-no-verify-package-signature
Skip GPG signature verification.
.TP
.B \-\-license
Display a short license notice.
.TP
.B \-\-license-all
Display the full GPL-3.0 license text.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show nhopkg version, copyright, and build-time configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show the built-in help page.
.TP
.B \-\-
Stop argument parsing. Everything after is treated as a package name.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
Fallback default configuration (shipped with the package).
.TP
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/packages/
Database of installed packages (one file per package).
.TP
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/files/
List of files installed by each package (compressed).
.TP
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/nhopkg.db
Locate-style database for dependency resolution.
.TP
.I /var/cache/nhopkg/
Downloaded packages and temporary files.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
General error (invalid arguments, missing package, etc.).
.TP
2
Insufficient privileges (must be root for most operations).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg.conf (5),
.BR nhoget (8),
.BR nhopkg-src (8),
.BR nhopkg-repos (8),
.BR nhouser (8),
.BR nhopkg-overlay (8)
